              <span id="reviewTextContainer146624243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8724504920719137253">I read this ages ago and loved it, and then recently listened to it with my kids. The narration is by Brendan Fraser and is awesome! I don&apos;t know if Cornelia Funke picked him to be Inkheart before or after he had narrated this book, but I can see why she did. He&apos;s amazing. Oh yeah, the story is good too. :) It&apos;s a nice journey, with fun characters and a bit of mystery and suspense. Great for kids in the 6-8 range, whereas the Inkheart books are really for a slightly older crowd. </span>
  <span id="freeText8724504920719137253" style="display:none">I read this ages ago and loved it, and then recently listened to it with my kids. The narration is by Brendan Fraser and is awesome! I don't know if Cornelia Funke picked him to be Inkheart before or after he had narrated this book, but I can see why she did. He's amazing. Oh yeah, the story is good too. :) It's a nice journey, with fun characters and a bit of mystery and suspense. Great for kids in the 6-8 range, whereas the Inkheart books are really for a slightly older crowd. </span>
